canonical:
  title: 西都
  author: 鄭知常
  language: lzh
  text: 紫陌春風細雨過輕塵不動柳絲斜綠䆫朱戶笙歌咽盡是梨園弟子家
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 西都
  author: 鄭知常
  language: lzh
  text: 紫陌春風細雨過。輕塵不動柳絲斜。綠䆫朱戶笙歌咽。盡是梨園弟子家。
korean:
  title: 서도
  author: 정지상
  language: kor
  text: |-
    번화론 거리 봄바람에 보슬비 지나간 뒤
    가벼운 티끌조차 일지 않고 버들개지만 휘늘어졌다
    푸른 창 붉은 문에 흐느끼는 노랫가락
    이 모두 다 이원제자(梨園弟子)의 집이라네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0220_020_0440&viewSync=OT
  footnotes:
  - key: '[주-D001] 이원제자(梨園弟子)의 집이라네 : '
    value: 당나라 현종(玄宗)이 이원(梨園)에 악부(樂部)를 설치하고, 남녀를 모아 음악을 가르쳤다.
english:
  title: The Western Capital
  author: Jeong Jigsang
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Through the purple streets, spring wind carries fine rain—
    Soft dust doesn't stir, only willow branches sway.
    Green shutters, vermillion doors—songs of sorrow seep through,
    Every house here belongs to the disciples of the Pear Garden.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The Pear Garden (梨園) refers to a prestigious music academy established by Tang Emperor Xuanzong, where both men and women were trained in the musical arts. By extension, it evokes a world of refined culture and courtly elegance.
